@page "/privacy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy</PageTitle>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="Pages/ContentPage.css" />

<div class="content-page">
    <FluentBreadcrumb>
        <FluentBreadcrumbItem Href="/">Home</FluentBreadcrumbItem>
        <FluentBreadcrumbItem Href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</FluentBreadcrumbItem>
    </FluentBreadcrumb>

    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>Commitment to Privacy</h2>
        <p>
            The National Benchmark Tests Project (NBT) is committed to protecting the privacy and personal information 
            of all users. This policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your information in compliance 
            with the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA) and other applicable legislation.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 2025</p>
    </FluentCard>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>Personal Information</h3>
        <p>When you register for the NBT, we collect:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Full names and surname</li>
            <li>South African ID number, Foreign ID, or Passport number</li>
            <li>Date of birth and gender</li>
            <li>Ethnicity (for equity research purposes)</li>
            <li>Contact details (email address, phone number, physical address)</li>
            <li>School and academic information</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Test Information</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Test booking details (venue, date, test type)</li>
            <li>Payment information and transaction records</li>
            <li>Test results and performance data</li>
            <li>Special accommodation requests</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Technical Information</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>IP address and browser information</li>
            <li>Website usage patterns and navigation</li>
            <li>Login timestamps and session data</li>
        </ul>
    </FluentCard>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>Your information is used for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Test Administration:</strong> Processing registrations, bookings, and test delivery</li>
            <li><strong>Results Delivery:</strong> Providing your NBT results to you and (with consent) to universities</li>
            <li><strong>Payment Processing:</strong> Managing test fees and payment confirmations</li>
            <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Sending test reminders, updates, and important notices</li>
            <li><strong>Research:</strong> Aggregated, anonymized data for educational research and test validation</li>
            <li><strong>Support Services:</strong> Responding to queries and providing customer support</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> Meeting regulatory and legal requirements</li>
        </ul>
    </FluentCard>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>Information Sharing</h2>
        <p>We share your information only in specific circumstances:</p>
        
        <h3>With Your Consent</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Universities and institutions you apply to (results only)</li>
            <li>Parents/guardians (if you are under 18)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Service Providers</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Payment gateway providers (EasyPay) for secure payment processing</li>
            <li>Email and SMS service providers for communications</li>
            <li>IT infrastructure and security providers</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Legal Requirements</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>When required by law or court order</li>
            <li>To protect rights, property, or safety</li>
        </ul>

        <FluentMessageBar Intent="MessageIntent.Info">
            We never sell your personal information to third parties.
        </FluentMessageBar>
    </FluentCard>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement comprehensive security measures to protect your information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> All data transmissions use HTTPS/TLS encryption</li>
            <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Strict role-based access to personal data</li>
            <li><strong>Secure Storage:</strong> Data stored in secure, access-controlled databases</li>
            <li><strong>Regular Audits:</strong> Ongoing security assessments and updates</li>
            <li><strong>Staff Training:</strong> All staff trained in data protection practices</li>
        </ul>
    </FluentCard>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your information for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Data:</strong> Duration of account plus 7 years (for potential future test bookings)</li>
            <li><strong>Test Results:</strong> Permanently (results valid for 3 years; historical record maintained)</li>
            <li><strong>Payment Records:</strong> 7 years (tax and audit requirements)</li>
            <li><strong>Research Data:</strong> Indefinitely in anonymized, aggregated form</li>
        </ul>
    </FluentCard>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Under POPIA, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal information</li>
            <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Update or correct inaccurate information</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion (subject to legal retention requirements)</li>
            <li><strong>Objection:</strong> Object to certain processing activities</li>
            <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Receive your data in a portable format</li>
            <li><strong>Complaint:</strong> Lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>To exercise your rights, contact us at: <strong>privacy@nbt.ac.za</strong></p>
    </FluentCard>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Maintain your login session</li>
            <li>Remember your preferences</li>
            <li>Analyze website usage and improve user experience</li>
            <li>Ensure security and prevent fraud</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can control cookie settings through your browser, but some features may not function properly without cookies.</p>
    </FluentCard>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
            Most NBT users are under 18. We collect only necessary information and require parental/guardian consent 
            for applicants under 18. Parents/guardians can access and manage their child's account information.
        </p>
    </FluentCard>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this privacy policy periodically. Material changes will be communicated via email or 
            website notice. Continued use of our services after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
    </FluentCard>

    <FluentCard class="info-card">
        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>For privacy-related questions or concerns:</p>
        <p>
            <strong>Email:</strong> privacy@nbt.ac.za<br/>
            <strong>Phone:</strong> 021 650 3523<br/>
            <strong>Address:</strong> Centre for Educational Assessment, University of Cape Town, Private Bag X1, Rondebosch 7701
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Information Officer:</strong> As required by POPIA, our Information Officer can be contacted at the above details.
        </p>
    </FluentCard>
</div>

